AB  - This paper describes a WAP-based course registration system designed and implemented to facilitating the process of students' registration at Bahrain University. The framework will support many opportunities for applying WAP based technology to many services such as wireless commerce, cashless payment… and location-based services. The paper outlines the main concepts of the analysis and design methodology of our proposed system. It shows also how the request will be issued, received, processed, formulated, and how the reply is sent back to the student for display.
